[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = HexWorld","category":"page"},{"location":"#HexWorld","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [HexWorld]","category":"page"},{"location":"#HexWorld.cell_materials","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.cell_materials","text":"CellWallType\n\nDifferent wall types\n\nAllowed Values: 1:16\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#HexWorld.cell_properties","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.cell_properties","text":"CellProperty\n\nGeneric cell wall properties\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#HexWorld.Cell","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.Cell","text":"Cell\n\nq: column index, starting from 1\nr: row index, starting from 1\n\nNote: \n\n(1,1) represents the upper left corner.\nIn Hexagons notation this structure   would have been called HexagonOffsetOddQ\n\nUnits:\n\nlength of a hexagon side is 1\nwidth is 2\nheight is sqrt(3)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.CellData","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.CellData","text":"Describes a Hexagonal Cell in a grid.\n\ntype::UInt8: points to unique CellMaterial\nheigth::UInt8: physical height of the cell\nwalls::SVector{6,UInt8}: wall meterial IDs from WallMaterial\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.CellData-Tuple{UInt64}","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.CellData","text":"CellData(pack)\n\nUnpacks the bytest into CellData structure\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HexWorld.CellMaterial","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.CellMaterial","text":"Materials used to describ cell's geometyr and physics.\n\nEach material has an unique id::UInt8 and type::String to identify  the type of the material.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.Cubic","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.Cubic","text":"Cubic\n\nHexagon represented as the intersection of the unit qube with the plane x + y + z = 1\n\nSee Cubic coordinates\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.EdgeCells","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.EdgeCells","text":"Defines an rectangel inside the gfrid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.Grid","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.Grid","text":"Grid\n\nRpresents a hexagonal grid. The coordinates are releted to  cells as odd-q, see  Hexagonal Grids\n\nParams:\n\ndims::GridDims: dimensions of the grid\ncells::Array{UInt64,2}: packed cell data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.GridDims","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.GridDims","text":"Grid Dimensions\n\nFields:\n\nwidth: number of columns (q cooridinate)\nheight: number of rows (r coordinate)  \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.Hex","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.Hex","text":"Hex\n\nHexagonal cell of a hex grid. Its implementations use different coordinate systesms\n\nSee Hexagonal Grids\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#HexWorld.WallMaterial","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.WallMaterial","text":"WallMaterial describes wall of a grid cell.\n\nid: composed of CellWallType and CellProperty\ncolor: refers to a collor in Color package.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Base.iterate","page":"Home","title":"Base.iterate","text":"i   terate(dims, state)\n\nIterates over the grid edge in clockwise direction starting  at upper left corener.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#HexWorld.cell_id-Tuple{UInt8,UInt8}","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.cell_id","text":"cell_id(t, p:)\n\nCreates wall id by or-ing type and property bits.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HexWorld.cemter_and_vertices_loc-Tuple{Cell}","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.cemter_and_vertices_loc","text":"cemterandvertices_loc(cell)\n\nReturns an 7 by 2 Array{Float64,2} where the first row is the center of the cell and other 6 rows contain vertices.\n\nVertices are orthered counter-clockwise, starting with the right-most vertex.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HexWorld.center_loc-Tuple{Cell}","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.center_loc","text":"center_loc(cell)\n\nReturns the (x,y) location of the center of the cell.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HexWorld.create_oval-Tuple{Any,EdgeCells,Cell,Grid,UInt64,UInt64}","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.create_oval","text":"createoval(f, rect, center:, grid, edgep, inner_p)\n\nUses rays between each cell on the boundary of the rectangle rect and the center, that is assumed to be inside the rect, and the function f to create a  shape in the interior of the rect.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HexWorld.pack_cell_data-Tuple{CellData}","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.pack_cell_data","text":"packcelldata(c)\n\nPacks the values of a CellData structure into 64bits.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#HexWorld.parse_cell_id-Tuple{UInt8}","page":"Home","title":"HexWorld.parse_cell_id","text":"parsecellid(w)\n\nReturns Material Type and Property\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
